        "text": "Sleep serves multiple essential brain functions: it consolidates memories from short-term to long-term storage, clears metabolic waste through the glymphatic system, repairs neural connections, regulates emotional reactivity, and restores prefrontal cortex function. Without adequate sleep, all of these processes are compromised."
      }
    },
