        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The glymphatic system is the brain's waste clearance network — a system of channels that uses cerebrospinal fluid to flush out metabolic byproducts during sleep, including amyloid-beta and tau proteins linked to Alzheimer's disease. It is most active during deep slow-wave sleep and nearly inactive during waking hours."
