      <section id="conclusion">
        <h2>Sleep Is the Foundation, Not the Ceiling</h2>
        <ContentBox type="tip" title="The Core Insight">
          <p>Every high-performance strategy — whether productivity, creativity, emotional regulation, or decision quality — operates on a foundation of sleep. You cannot optimize the superstructure while neglecting the foundation. The research is unambiguous: the brain that sleeps well learns faster, decides better, recovers from stress more completely, and ages more slowly. Treating sleep as a performance variable rather than a lifestyle preference is one of the highest-leverage shifts a serious achiever can make. Your nights do not follow your days — they determine them.</p>
        </ContentBox>
      </section>

